a. list the system calls required for file creation, writing, reading, and closing.
the system calls needed are OPEN(), WRITE(), READ(), and CLOSE(). OPEN() is used to create or open a file, WRITE() is used to write data into the file, READ() is used to read the contents of the file, and CLOSE() is used to close the file after the work is completed.
b. explain the purpose of any two file management system calls.
the OPEN() system call is used to create a new file or open an existing file so that it can be used for reading or writing. the WRITE() system call is used to store data inside the file. these system calls help the operating system manage files properly and safely.
